Alert Title: Suspicious Login from New Location

Alert ID: SOC-FP-001

Alert Severity: Medium

Alert Status: False Positive – Closed

Who
•	User Account: a.smith
•	Role: Finance Manager
•	Device: FIN-LAP-07

What
The SIEM generated an alert for a login attempt from a new geographic location not previously associated with the user account.

When
•	Timestamp: 2025-01-13 08:15 UTC

Where
•	Source IP: 192.168.44.12
•	Location: Remote VPN Gateway

Why (Verdict Reasoning)
The login was confirmed as legitimate.
The user was working remotely and successfully authenticated via the company VPN.
Authentication logs show a valid VPN session established prior to the login event, and no additional suspicious activity was observed.

Actions Taken
•	VPN logs reviewed and correlated with SIEM alert
•	User activity monitored for anomalies (none found)
•	Alert marked as False Positive and closed

Escalation Decision
•	No escalation required
•	Activity aligned with expected user behavior

Notes
This alert highlights the importance of correlating VPN and authentication logs before escalation.

